Summary of Important Directories:
1. / – Root directory, base of the file system.
2. /bin & /sbin – Essential binaries and system binaries.
3. /etc – Configuration files.
4. /home – User directories.
5. /lib – Shared libraries.
6. /usr – User binaries, libraries, and local software.
7. /var – Variable data like logs and spools. 
8. /tmp – Temporary files.
9. /dev – Device files.
10. /proc & /sys – System information.
11. /boot – Bootloader files.
